register.description: Specifies the PIR idle increment value

bitfield.description: The number added to the PIR counter every clock cycle. If 0, the PIR counter is disabled and packets will never be marked or processed as RED.

bitfield.description: The number added to the CIR counter every clock cycle. If 0, the CIR counter is disabled.

register.description: The Policing Table Control is used to read or write the selected policing/classifier entry

bitfield.description: Setting this bit will write the POLICER_CFG 0-7 to the pol_tbl_index selected policing/classifier entry
This field specifies the policing/classifier entry to be read or written

register.description: The Control Enables color marking as well as internal ALE packet dropping

bitfield.description: Enables the policing to color the packets. This also enables red or yellow drop capabilities.
Policing Match Mode determines what happens to packets that fail to hit any policing/classifier entry

register.description: The Policing Test Control enables the ability to determine which policing entry has been hit and whether they reported a red or yellow rate condition

bitfield.description: Policer Clear - This bit clears all the policer/classifier hit bits (policer_hit, policer_hit_red, and policer_hit_yellow bits for all policer/classifiers)
Policer Clear RED - This bit clears all policer/classifier RED hit bits (policer_hit_red for all policer/classifiers)
Policer Clear YELLOW - This bit clears all policer/classifier YELLOW hit bits (policer_hit_yellow for all policer/classifiers)
Policer Clear Selected - This bit clears the selected policer/classifier policer_hit, policer_hit_red, and policer_hit_yellow bits
Policer Test Entry Pointer - This field selects the policer/classifier entry that will have hit bits read or written

register.description: The policing hit status is a read only register that reads the hit bits of the selected policing/classifier

bitfield.description: This indicates that the selected policing/classifier via the pol_test_index field has been hit by a packet seen on any port that matches the policing/classifier entry match.
This indicates that the selected policing/classifier via the pol_test_index field has been hit during a RED condition by a packet seen on any port that matches the policing/classifier entry match.
This indicates that the selected policing/classifier via the pol_test_index field has been hit during a YELLOW condition by a packet seen on any port that matches the policing/classifier entry match.

register.description: The THREAD Mapping Default Value register is used to set the default thread ID when no classifier is matched

bitfield.description: This field is the read or written enable for the Default Thread ID. When set, the switch will use the def_thread_val for the default thread ID if no classifier is matched. If clear, the switch will generate its own thread ID based on port and priority if there is no classifier match.
This field is the read or written default thread ID value that is used for host traffic.

register.description: The THREAD Mapping Control register allows the highest matched classifier to return a particular thread ID for traffic sent to the host
The THREAD Mapping Value register is used to set the thread ID for a particular classifier entry

bitfield.description: This field is the read or written enable for the Thread ID. When set, the switch will use the thread_val for the particular classifier match. If clear, the switch will generate its own thread ID based on port and priority.
This field is the read or written thread ID value that is used to map a classifier hit to thread ID for host traffic.

register.description: Port N Control Offset = 0003E040h + (y * 4h); where y = 0h to 1h
